{
  "stem": "12255.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And shortly after the Bergen-Belsen camp had been liberated, there was a dire need for at least one or two men, who had some authority, who could represent the displaced persons, as they were then called, who could care for them, could act as liaison for them, with the British forces.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so, I and another Jewish chaplain were posted immediately-- we had about a week's notice-- were posted to Bergen-Belsen direct.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we took off from London.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On the 8th of May.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "VE day, and you can imagine, Piccadilly circus.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a real circus.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had to report to a little office there, and we got on the bus and were taken to the airport and flew out from England.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we landed in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We couldn't get transport on for a day or two, so we spent the evening in Brussels.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And a day or two later, we landed at an airport near to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were met by the senior Jewish chaplain, known as Isaac Levy, or Ike Levy, and he took us over to Bergen-Belsen, and, as it were, threw us head-first into what was obviously a tremendously strange experience to us.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, of course, we witnessed the horror of all that was going on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Those who survived were-- had barely survived, and for weeks, many hundreds of people were still dying from the effects of starvation, and even some from the effects of eating the wrong food when the [?",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Tommies, ?] out of the goodness of their heart, gave them tins of bully beef, and food like that, which the-- what is the word-- their stomachs just couldn't--",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Rejected it.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--couldn't-- couldn't take-- take in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The films, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Seen the-- Oh, yes we'd seen 'em.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Idea of what-- yeah.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
